Package: spThin
Type: Package
Title: Functions for Spatial Thinning of Species Occurrence Records for Use in
    Ecological Models
Version: 0.1.1
Date: 2015-07-12
Author: Matthew E. Aiello-Lammens, Robert A. Boria, Aleksandar Radosavljevic,
    Bruno Vilela, and Robert P. Anderson
Maintainer: Matthew E. Aiello-Lammens <matt.lammens@gmail.com>
Description: spThin contains functions to spatially filter and thin species
    occurrence data. These procedures can remove sampling bias, and in turn result
    in better ecological niche models. The package contains functions to thin
    datasets using exact-algorithm solvers (LpSolve and Gurobi) and a heuristic.
    To thin data using Gurobi, the gurobi R package will need to be installed from
    http://www.gurobi.com/.
Imports:
    Rcpp,
    RcppEigen
Depends:
    sp,
    knitr,
    ggplot2,
    gridExtra,
    raster,
    rgeos,
    lpSolveAPI,
    Matrix
LinkingTo: Rcpp,
    RcppEigen
LazyData: TRUE
License: GPL-3
VignetteBuilder: knitr
Suggests:
    testthat
Enhances: gurobi
Collate:
